----------------------------------
INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS
----------------------------------

ATTENTION: with Debian, you will be need to change the name of the cron files as Debian don't like filename with a dot (.) in name.

-------------------------------------------
Database cleanup of maillog records
-------------------------------------------

Add db_clean.php to /etc/cron.daily/

You need to edit conf.php the RECORD_DAYS_TO_KEEP definition.

You may need to edit the db_clean.php to reflect the location of the functions.php file.

--------------------------------------------
Quarantine Maintenance
--------------------------------------------

quarantine_maint.php
quarantine_maint.sh

Add quarantine_maint.sh to /etc/cron.daily/
Add quarantine_maint.php to /usr/local/bin/

Delete the clean.quarantine cron (MailScanner v4).

Change the variable for Quarantine Retention to "q_days=0" in /etc/MailScanner/defaults (MailScanner v5).

You will need to edit in conf.php the QUARANTINE_DAYS_TO_KEEP definition.

You may need to edit the quarantine_maint.php to reflect the location of the functions.php file.

--------------------------------------------
Quarantine Report
--------------------------------------------

quarantine_report.php

Add it to /etc/cron.daily

You will need to edit the quarantine_report.php to reflect the location of the functions.php file.

--------------------------------------------
MailScanner Rule Editor
--------------------------------------------

msre_reload.crond

See the instructions in tools/MailScanner_rule_editor/INSTALL

Add it to /etc/cron.d when you have properly configured and installed msre_reload.sh.

